The ultrasound showed gallstones, cholecystitis, and dilation of the common bile duct;  
Gastroscopy showed chronic superficial gastritis with erosions;  
Serum amylase (AMY) was 2642 IU/L;  
Urine amylase (UAMY) was 2315 IU/L;  
Abdominal CT showed necrotizing pancreatitis, gallstones, and bilateral pleural effusion.
